1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with image reconstruction and motion tracking, which are core topics in computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a novel subspace learning framework that utilizes tensor decomposition and Tykhonov regularization, which are common techniques in machine learning. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of randomized subsampling policies to accelerate the acquisition process, which is related to information theory and signal processing. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper proposes an optimization algorithm based on alternating majorization minimization, which is a common technique in numerical analysis. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with real-time reconstruction of MRI images, which is a multimedia application.
